this is a c&p of a bad pattern for two reasons:

the message if available should be explaining that it is a uri syntax issue.
as in most of the other catch clauses this can be replaced by something like String.format("%s: %s", e.getClass().getSimpleName(), e.getMessage()). And we should then unify the catch clauses.

I suggest replacing with (something like):
        } catch (final TimeoutException e) {
            s_logger.debug("Timed out while migrating domain: " + e.getMessage());
            result = e.getMessage();
        } catch (final IOException
                | ParserConfigurationException
                | SAXException
                | TransformerException
                | URISyntaxException e) {
            s_logger.debug(String.format("%s: %s", e.getClass().getSimpleName(), e.getMessage()));
            result = "Exception during migrate, see hypervisor for details; " + e.getMessage();
        } finally {

